<br>
I'm playing a post 50 melee for the first time and I was hoping someone could direct me to a resource that explains the special attacks of high level NPC's and strategies on how to deal with them. Linking me to a guide would be ideal. I didn't see one in our guides section, so I'm asking here. <br>
<br>
My elite strategy thus far is when a mob starts doing any of this nuttiness, I get the hell behind it if I'm not there already and if I start taking random damage, I feign.  Somehow, I think I might be screwing up. (ya think? Hehe).  <br>
<br>
Anyway, people always say Rampage tanking is for monks due to FD and how it interacts.  Why?  Under what circumstances?  I was on a Vindi raid and nothing special was done to accomodate the rampages.  We just all got out of the way.<br>
<br>
I almost posted this in the newbie zone, but thought maybe it was better for the main page. <br>
