Thanks <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucatranizi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Catranizi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>The Froglok Monk<br>Frrroooaaak!!!</b></span><br>  Posts: 1515<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 12:15:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1047.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rampage, Flurry, Enraged - Questions</span><hr size=1> Flurry: extra set of attack per round. Will only affect your MT.<br>
<br>
Enrage: Mobs that are melee type will enrage, ie, autoriposte all your frontal hits. It's fine if you attack from back but watch for turning mobs or you'll be puree.<br>
<br>
Rampage: Mob will do an attack round on one extra person other than MT. I'm sure there will be 20 people that will say rampage hit 5 more targets, but that's because the rampage people keep dying. It's really 1 more person. Depending on the encounters, you will have to learn how to deal with it. It can go from healing the small damage (Vindicator rampages rarely, for example) to other strategies (Arch Lich rampages every round). The fun part is figuring the boss mob fights.<br>
<br>
Rampages from non-boss mobs can be disregarded with small healing from druids and such. <p>[60 Grandmaster] <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=501>Catranizi</a> (Iksar) <a href=http://www.thealangroup.com/awakened/>Awakened</a><br><br><i>The Devil will find work for idle hands to do</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umidibrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Midi Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 12:25:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1047.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ya</span><hr size=1> Flurry will just effect the MT.  Its extra attacks verus one player.  I believe its 2 or 3 extra attacks. Slow and or cripple will reduce this.  If you arent the main target you wont get flurried on.   AOW or Tunare is in this category.<br>
<br>
<br>
Enrage is auto riptose to all hits when the mob gets under 10 percent HPs left.  It lasts for only a short while.  Be careful to be sure you are behind the mob when its that low on health.  Or turn off attack until enrage passes if you cant get behind the mob, or if MT stops attacking and mob turns. Only warrior or perhaps SK/Pal class mobs will enrage, and then only if level 55 or higher.  This is by far the thing you will have to deal with more than anything.  <br>
<br>
Rampage-what the previous poster said.  Its only 1 extra person that gets hit.  Learning how to stay off that list, and how to get another plate type tank onto that rampage spot is key to a lot of fights like Arch Lich or High Priest.  Likewise, you need your raids clerics to dedicate extra heals to the rampagee. Other rampagers include Creator, Vindi, Dain. <p><FONT SIZE=2><P></FONT><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=121079"><FONT SIZE=2>FluFlu’s toys<FONT></A></P></BODY>
</HTML></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzikoz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zikoz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 490<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 12:58:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1047.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ya</span><hr size=1> So, it sounds like Rampage is the one that I need to worry about.  It seems that this is the one that could surprise you and you could just end up *dead* pretty fast.  Until I learn exactly how the hate lists work with 4 bajillion people all beating on stuff, it will be hard to know what's what.<br>
<br>
Enraged, is within my ability to control. If I'm watching my hits, I'll know when I'm being riposted, and the message is pretty clear. At that point, I just move to the back if I'm not there already.<br>
<br>
Flurry is no biggie and I don't imagine any surprises here.<br>
<br>
Now, two other questions.  <br>
<br>
The Monk/Rampage/FD strategy.  Please explain how and under what circumstances a monk should be prepared to deal with this.<br>
<br>
Do ripostes from Enrage get coded as &quot;my misses&quot;? I've had those turned off in the new UI 'cause my hitsmode window had to be shrunk down.  I was taking damage, probably from an Enraged mob and I never saw the dmg. I really don't want to turn on my misses, but it sounds like I'll need to if I'm gonna end up splattered from an Enraged critter by not having misses on. Watching my HP is one thing, but nothing says &quot;uh oh&quot; like having red spam in my hits window.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunnieeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SunnieEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 1:06:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1047.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ya</span><hr size=1> Ripostes that hit will show up as &quot;mob hits me&quot;.  Also there is a text string that indicated the mob is flurrying/rampaging/enraging.  You can alter that color, pick something that's going to stand out.  <br>
