 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50482>Sunnie</a><BR>53 druid, Prexus<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55033>Stephania</a><BR>53 monk, Prexus<BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunnieeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SunnieEQ</A> at: 8/20/02 1:08:03 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uallesh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Allesh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 3:24:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1047.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rampage, Flurry, Enraged - Questions</span><hr size=1> The text string for enrage is something like...<br>
&quot;Soandso has become ENRAGED&quot; and &quot;Soandso is no longer enraged&quot;<br>
<br>
If you miss seeing that and nobody says &quot;watch enrage,&quot; you can probably figure out that the mob is enraged by looking at the number of hits you are taking.  If you go from taking no hits to taking a bunch really fast (or from taking a few to taking a bunch really fast in the event you were tanking), then the mob has probably enraged.<br>
<br>
Its good habit to turn off attack whenever you get hit if you don't want to be tanking something since, unless you keep attack on and wait, you can't tell the difference between a riposte and the first of many hits (because you have misses turned off).  If you turn off attack and back up for just a few seconds when you get hit, you will avoid taking agro when you don't want it, and be prepared for avoiding enrage if youi miss the message. <p>Brother Yoso Limplizard</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunnieeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SunnieEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 181<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 4:03:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1047.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rampage, Flurry, Enraged - Questions</span><hr size=1> Although there is something to be said for not seeing the message, getting riposted up the wazzu before finally turning off attack, and realized all but a couple actually hit (miss, miss, miss, dodge, block, block, hit, hit, riposte, etc).  =P <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50482>Sunnie</a><BR>53 druid, Prexus<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55033>Stephania</a><BR>53 monk, Prexus<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiskys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iskys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 318<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 4:15:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=