ers) are added to the bottom of the list as they are put on the mob's hate list.<br>
<br>
You can move in and out of melee range and put rampage on someone else, but it won't change your position on the list. If you come back into melee range closer than the 2nd person for instance, you'll be back on rampage. Learning how to control rampage and heal rampage tanks is key to a lot of Luclin encounters. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=736" target="_blank"><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~sinman/webshots/soysig.jpg"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiskys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iskys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 328<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/21/02 9:36:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1047.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rampage, Flurry, Enraged - Questions</span><hr size=1> Guess i missed something ! So now I know there is only one rampager <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     Most of the time, it's me who is taking those extra hits, I love acting like those big tanks although I never allowed to do so. At least for rampages I am sure I will keep them on me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
