Rampage does not hit 2 people, it hits 1 person, and thats whoever entered the mobs hatelist first and is still in melee range, and has generated hate (attacking or spells) within the last 5 minutes (ie you can fall off the rampage list if you do nothing).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is probably best explination here on rampage. will add some more to it. It hits the MT or procs off him + 1 other target. wich is stated above. Its first person to get aggro will get first rampage slot 2nd person will be next up in line if 1st dies or moves OOR. You keep rampage if you die and are res'd back in under a certain amount of time. Fd has a RARE chance of removing you from rampage list VERY rare but is possible. Only way to move up or down on rampage while fighting is VIA enchanter hate -/+ spells. They will move you on rampage list once spell weres off you go to orginal spot on list.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udakkin2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dakkin2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/22/02 2:11:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1047.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rampage, Flurry, Enraged - Questions</span><hr size=1> Lots of useful information here from various people.  I haven't seen a guide on high level aggro management Zikoz, so just in case they're handy, here are a couple of extra tips:<br>
<br>
1)  Wait till the MT has engaged for several seconds before attacking.  Lets him build up a good taunt to keep aggro off you.<br>
<br>
2)  Make a hotbutton with the following lines:<br>
/attack off<br>
/doability 1 (where FD is enabled on ability button 1, say)<br>
/stand<br>
/attack on<br>
Use this whenever FD pops throughout the fight; makes aggro control through FD much less painful.<br>
<br>
3)  Try to stay at maximum melee range; hate is very dependent on your distance from the mob.  Edge back every few seconds till you see the &quot;out of range&quot; message then edge back in again.<br>
<br>
There are many different opinions about the mechanics of rampage, but in my experience the above 3 points seem to help a lot in avoiding it.<br>
<br>
4)  If you get aggro, don't just FD (in many circumstances at high levels FD doesn't work if you're in melee range of the mob).  Take attack off, start to back up and quickly hit FD while still backing away.  With luck this will FD you out of melee range of the mob.  DON'T stand up immediately...give the MT a good 5 or 10 seconds to get good aggro on the mob again.<br>
<br>
5)  If fighting a mob which you know enrages, use a 2Hb if you reasonably can; if worst comes to worst and someone turns him so he's facing you when he rages, there's a fantastic difference between getting one or two ripostes with a slowish 2Hb and getting 5 or 10 with a couple of fast 1Hbs before you can react.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps,<br>
<br>
