<br>
If you know you have a slow connection, and are lagging and using two fast 1HB/HtH weapons from a frontal position, stop attacking before you see the message. Because by then it's too late if your lagging. Either get behind the mob, or switch to a 2HB and risk it, or stop and wait for Enrage to end. Dying to enrage and &quot;blaming&quot; lag is not a good excuse.<br>
<br>
Flurry is an extra set of attacks via a &quot;proc&quot;, normally (but not always) on the MA. &quot;Proc rates&quot; of flurry differ from mob to mob. Cripple line of spells will reduce the &quot;proc rate&quot; of Flurry.. so they flurry less. A slowed mob also procs less, so flurries less.<br>
<br>
Chanter based mem wipe spells clear the rampage list... yes, even against very high level mobs. Esp usefull on rooted mobs.<br>
<br>
FD temporarily suspends you from the rampage list... and the next (2nd) person in the list gets hit next rampage. But as soon as you get up, your back 1st on the list. Make sure if you (a monk) are on rampage, and you FD that you say so, else healers will switch to the next person, and then when you get back up you will not get healed.<br>
<br>
When pulling a rampage mob, tell your bards to stop singing (esp AoE songs). Because if they don't, you can be sure they will be high up on the rampage list.<br>
<br>
Before rezing someone who dies to rampage <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>during a fight</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, drag their corpse away. Otherwise, when rezed they will be pretty much immediately killed.<br>
<br>
It's very very important that if you get onto rampage, you tell your guild asap. Otherwise you will almost definately die.<br>
<br>
I've been rampage tank on many mobs, either intentionally or unintentionally, and seen several boss mob fights lost due to rampage, and people not managing it. Set-up some hot keys to tell your guild if you need to. Remember, it's your responsibility as much as the guilds to manage rampage.<br>
